30/01/2005
OHRID, Macedonia -- The Albanian and Macedonian interior ministers, Igli Toska and Ljubomir Mihajlovski, met in Ohrid Friday (28 January) to discuss joint initiatives in combating organised crime and trafficking.
They described the bilateral co-operation against trafficking as successful.
The two ministries are reportedly preparing to establish joint police patrols along the Albanian-Macedonian border.
In other news, Austria's newly-appointed ambassador to Albania, Klaus Derkowitsch, pledged his country's continued support for Albanian efforts towards Euro-Atlantic integration.
He presented his credentials to President Alfred Moisiu on Friday.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Albanian News - 29/01/05)
